doc.title: Electronic Components | Japan July HDD/SSD Data? DC Demand Remaining Solid for Both HDDs & SSDs

passages.text: August 29, 2025 10:43 AM GMT

Shipment growth of DC NL HDDs is expected to be limited due to constraints in media and head production capacity. Attention is now focused on whether TDK will resume supplying heads to companies other than Toshiba.

DC NL HDD production rose YoY, fell slightly MoM; shipment growth remains limited due to capacity constraints, but capacity per unit & ASP should continue up. Ongoing shortage of heads and media for NL HDDs; attention on whether TDK will resume head supply to companies other than Toshiba. Capacity per unit is increasing more noticeably in DC- oriented enterprise SSDs.

July HDD output \(+2.8\%\) YoY, \(+1.2\%\) MoM: July HDD production volume announced by Techno Systems Research (TSR) on Aug 29 was 10.95mn units (10.65mn a year ago, 10.82mn a month ago). HDD output declined from 261.70mn units in 2021 (- 0.1% YoY) to 168.70mn in 2022 (- 35.5%) and 120.51mn in 2023 (- 28.6%), before recovering to 124.77mn units in 2024 (+3.5%). Quarterly output was 29.80mn units in Jan- Mar 2024 (- 10.1% YoY, +1.7% QoQ), 31.16mn in Apr- Jun (+7.4%, +4.6%), 32.30mn in Jul- Sep (+11.2%, +3.7%), and 31.51mn in Oct- Dec (+7.5%, - 2.4%). In 2025, output has been 31.01mn units (+4.1% YoY, - 1.6% QoQ) in Jan- Mar, and 31.68mn units (+2.2%, +1.7%) in Apr- Jun. TSR forecasts total HDD output for 2025 at 128.90mn units (+3.3% YoY, previous forecast: 128.80mn), incl 33.20mn units (+2.8% YoY, +4.8% QoQ) in Jul- Sep, and 33.01mn units (+4.8%, +0.6%) in Oct- Dec. Our shipment forecasts are shown in Exhibit 4 and differ from TSR's production estimates.

July output of NL HDDs for DCs (data centers) \(+13.7\%\) YoY, - 0.6% MoM: July near- line (NL) HDD output was 6.22mn units (5.47mn a year ago, 6.26mn a month ago). Full- year N output volume: 814.5mn units (+18.0% YoY) in 2021, 71.30mn (- 12.5%) in 2022, 44.51mn (- 37.6%) in 2023, 63.12mn (+41.8%) in 2024. By quarter, output in 2024 was 13.60mn units (+8.7% YoY, +17.2% QoQ) in Jan- Mar, 15.38mn (+4.8%, +1.8%) in Apr- Jun, 16.90mn (+59.4%, +9.9%) in Jul- Sep, and 17.24mn (+45.0%, +0.8%) in Oct- Dec. In 2025, output has been 17.32mn (+27.4%, +0.5%) in Jan- Mar, and 18.37mn (+19.4%, +6.1%) in Apr- Jun. TSR forecasts 2025 total output of 74.20mn (+17.5% YoY, previous forecast: 74.20mn), incl. 19.10mn in Jul- Sep (+13.0% YoY, +4.0% QoQ), and 19.40mn in Oct- Dec (+12.5%, +1.6%).
MORGAN STANLEY MUFG SECURITIES CO., LTD.

July SSD shipment vol. \(+6.8\%\) YoY, \(- 2.6\%\) MoM: July SSD shipments came to 30.87mn units (28.90mn a year ago, 31.70mn a month ago). Full- year: 383.02mn units (+21.4% YoY) in 2021, 34.8.30mn (- 9.1%) in 2022, 319.80mn (- 8.2%) in 2023, 34.8.20mn (+8.0%) in 2024. By quarter, total shipments were 84.10mn in Jan- Mar 2024 (+10.9% YoY, - 3.7% QoQ), 86.30mn in Apr- Jun (+13.3%, +2.6%), 88.70mn in Jul- Sep (+10.2%, +2.8%), 89.10mn in Oct- Dec (+2.1%, +0.5%), 86.90mn in Jan- Mar 2025 (+3.3%, - 2.5%), and 89.80mn in Apr- Jun (+3.3%, +4.1%). TSR forecasts 2025 total shipments of 366.00mn (+5.1% YoY), incl. 93.90mn in Jul- Sep (+11.3% YoY, +4.6% QoQ), and 95.40mn in Oct- Dec (+7.1%, +1.6%). Inventory adjustment affecting SSDs overall (including enterprise SSDs for data centers) through Apr- Jun has already been resolved, and TSR expects shipment volumes to continue increasing from Aug onward. The overall shipment capacity of SSDs and the average capacity per unit continue to show an uptrend. This increase is especially pronounced in enterprise SSDs for data center applications.

NL HDD shipment growth is limited, but capacity increase and ASP growth are expected to continue: As shown in Exhibit 4, we estimate that DC NL HDD shipments temporarily declined in Jan- Mar 2025 but have been gradually increasing since Apr- Jun. We forecast NL HDD shipments to reach 66.58mn units in 2025 (+13.7% YoY). While this remains below the 2021 peak of 73.50mn units in terms of volume, we expect 2025 HDD shipment capacity to reach 1,595EB, surpassing the 1,345EB recorded in 2021. This reflects our view that NL HDD shipment capacity will continue to grow. Although quarterly NL HDD production will likely rise only moderately due to constraints in media and head manufacturing capacity, shipments of high- capacity models of 24TB and above are increasing, and ASP is expected to continue rising.
